-- 2010-06-30T00:00:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/fonterra-says-proposed-new-capital-structure-will-buoy-project-spending.html

          
          
             Fonterra Cooperative Group Ltd., the
worldâ€™s largest dairy exporter, will have more to spend on plant
expansion once a new capital structure is approved, according to
Chief Executive Officer Andrew Ferrier.  
 The company expects to spend NZ$500 million ($346 million)
a year in New Zealand on capital projects, Ferrier said in a
speech. Farmer shareholders of the Auckland-based company vote
today on a proposal that will create permanent share capital and
remove the need for the company to set aside capital for
redemptions.   
          
          


  


        